## Local vs Lab Environment

The lab runs in a Linux cloud IDE with bash. On Windows PowerShell:

| Bash (lab) | PowerShell (local) |
|---|---|
| `source my_env/bin/activate` | `my_env\Scripts\Activate.ps1` |
| `python3.11 script.py` | `python script.py` (venv handles version) |
| `\` line continuation in pip install | Single-line pip install command |

The lab uses `project_id="skills-network"` as a free auth shortcut only available in their cloud IDE. Locally, use a real IBM Cloud API key stored in `.env` and loaded via `python-dotenv`.

